                <p class="text-justify">Avianca Airlines is the world's second-oldest airline based in Colombia founded in 1919. The airline’s focus cities are Barranquilla, Miami, and San José, in the latter of which Avianca is the largest foreign carrier by the number of passengers with a fleet size of 100 aircraft. Aviance rewards its loyal customers who frequently fly with the airline via a frequent flyer program called LifeMiles. </p>
