                <h2>Refund policy </h2>
                <p class="text-justify">According to <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/avianca-airlines-refund-policy.aspx">Avianca Airlines’ refund policy</a>, you will receive a refund according to your ticket’s fare conditions. The refundable amount will be made to the card/account of the person who paid for the ticket. If you wish to get tax refunds, you must request the same from the airline by calling customer care. The airline will refund surcharges and administrative fees as per applicable regulations, and if no such regulations exist, then as per the fare conditions of the ticket. </p>
                <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Who can receive a refund from Avianca Airlines? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Since you have purchased the ticket, you are eligible to receive a refund. To receive the refund, you must provide necessary documents confirming that you have paid for the ticket such as an invoice or credit card. However, if the person who paid for the ticket couldn’t collect a refund due to sickness or death, the refund will be issued to an immediate family member, after providing a death certificate or medical certificate. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">How can I cancel a flight ticket with Avianca Airlines? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">If you wish to cancel the flight ticket, you may call the Avianca Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. You can also visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Where can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">In order to make a request for a refund, you can visit the official website of Avianca Airlines and fill out the refund request form. The airline will process your refund within 7 to 20 business days.  </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Will I get compensation if my flight gets delayed by more than 2 hours? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">If your flight gets delayed by more than 2 hours, you are eligible to get compensation from the airline. If you are a member of LifeMiles then you will receive compensation in the form of LifeMiles. You may also receive EMD (Electronic Miscellaneous Document) or MPD (Multiple Purpose Document), a sum of money that you can use to buy services on Avianca Holdings. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Is my flight refundable? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Although such information is mentioned on the ticket, you can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number. It will display refund eligibility and information. </p>


